The paper discusses privacy leakage in the context of differential privacy, which is a topic commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also uses mathematical models to analyze the impact of data correlation, which is a topic relevant to data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper considers linear queries, which are commonly used in database systems (cs.DB).
